The painter gives evidence in the rape case in the mansion that he painted:
- I was standing on a stepladder, painting the wall near the second floor window. I noticed how some guy broke into the house, ran into the room and attacked the girl. He tore off her clothes, then he took off her bra and panties. He threw her on the bed and lay on top of her.
The judge listens attentively and says:
- So,
go on, the painter continued:
- I didn't see anything else, because the ladder broke and I fell down.
Judge:
- How did it break?
The painter says:
"Because twelve people have already stuck to her.
